description.narrative: Child participation is high on the European Union's agenda thanks to the adoption of the Bucharest EU Children's Declaration, facilitated by UNICEF, the Romanian Children's Board and the Romanian Government during Romania's presidency of the EU Council. Furthermore, child rights remained at the top of the country's agenda in 2019 as a result of renewed partnerships with the Romanian Government, Presidency, Parliament, corporate sector, NGOs, media, influencers and children. Adolescents shared their opinions and valuable insights with top European decision- makers. Over three per cent of national child-related news was generated as a result of UNICEF events and initiatives. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
